-- Japan Air to Submit Rehabilitation Plan to Lenders Today, Nikkei Reports
-- Yusuke Miyazawa
-- 2010-08-01T22:27:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-01/jal-to-submit-rehabilitation-plan-to-lender-banks-today-nikkei-reports.html

          
          
             Japan Airlines Corp. will present its
rehabilitation plan to lenders today, the Nikkei newspaper
reported, without saying where it obtained the information.  
 The company will seek waivers for 521.6 billion yen ($6
billion) in debt, the report said. Lenders are likely to approve
the proposal, it said.  
